  "prompt": "Do guys friendzone you because they dont want to lose you?",
  "response": "It's possible for someone to place you in the \"friend zone\" out of a desire to maintain a relationship without romantic involvement. They may value your friendship and want to keep you in their life, but might not feel a romantic connection or may be uncertain about their feelings. This can be influenced by various factors, such as fear of intimacy, past experiences, or simply a lack of attraction.\n\nUltimately, everyone's situation is unique, and motivations can vary widely among individuals. Open communication about feelings can often help clarify intentions and desires in any relationship.",
